# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback for the "One" web app (react-navigation web routes).
# Every unmatched path serves index.html with a 200 so client-side routing works
# (e.g. /profile/handle, /notifications) and deep links / refreshes don't 404.
# Cloudflare serves real static assets first; this only catches the misses.
#
# /static/* is EXCLUDED from the fallback: a missing content-hashed asset must
# 404, never serve index.html. The fallback at an asset path inherits the
# _headers year-long immutable Cache-Control for /static/*, so one request
# racing a deploy poisons the edge cache at that URL with HTML for a year and
# the app hangs on the splash screen (happened 2026-07-19 on main.d0e24bd6.js).
/static/*    /404.html    404
/*    /index.html    200
